# Backend (API) Documentation

The Praypure Backend is a Node.js/Express server that serves as the central API and database interface for both the main website and the admin panel, using MongoDB as the data store.

## Tech Stack
-   **Runtime**: Node.js
-   **Web Framework**: Express.js
-   **Database**: MongoDB (via Mongoose)
-   **Storage**: AWS S3 (for image uploads)
-   **Authentication**: JWT (JSON Web Tokens)
-   **Security**: CORS enabled for frontend/admin domains.

## API Architecture

### 1. Core Endpoints (Prefix: `/api`)
All routes are prefixed with `/api`. Key route groups include:
-   `/auth`: Login and authentication token generation.
-   `/products`: Product catalog management.
-   `/categories`: Store categorization logic.
-   `/content`: Management of hero slides, testimonials, and Instagram data.
-   `/subscribers`: Newsletter and email list management.
-   `/qrcodes`: QR code generation and tracking.
-   `/settings`: Global store settings.
-   `/upload`: Route for uploading images to AWS S3.

### 2. Middleware
-   `verifyToken`: Used on all protected routes to ensure only authenticated admins can modify data.
-   `cors`: Configured to allow traffic from `praypure.com` and `admin.praypure.com`.

### 3. Models (Database Schema)
-   `Product.js`: Fields for name, price, description, images, category, fragrance.
-   [Category.js](file:///c:/Users/Janvi%20Thakkar/OneDrive/Desktop/Praypure/backend/models/Category.js): Fields for title, slug, banner image, priority, and **status** (Live, Coming Soon, Invisible).
-   [InstagramPost.js](file:///c:/Users/Janvi%20Thakkar/OneDrive/Desktop/Praypure/backend/models/InstagramPost.js): Manages the manually curated Instagram gallery.
-   `Subscriber.js`: Stores customer email addresses.
-   `HeroSlide.js`: Configures the homepage banner.

## Environment Variables
Stored in the [.env](file:///c:/Users/Janvi%20Thakkar/OneDrive/Desktop/Praypure/admin/.env) file on the server:

| Variable | Description |
| :-- | :-- |
| `MONGODB_URI` | Connection string for MongoDB. |
| `PORT` | Local port for the server (usually 5000). |
| `JWT_SECRET` | Secret key for signing authentication tokens. |
| `AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID` | Access key for S3 bucket integration. |
| `AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY`| Secret key for S3 bucket integration. |
| `AWS_REGION` | S3 bucket region (e.g., `us-east-1`). |
| `AWS_BUCKET_NAME` | Name of the bucket where images are stored. |

## Git & Deployment
-   **Branch**: `backend`
-   **Deployment**: Automatically deployed to **Vercel** via the `backend` branch.
-   **Vercel Project**: `praypure-backend`
-   **URL**: `api.praypure.com`
